  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Roughly chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1654604526555-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1654604526555-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1654604526555-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1654604526555-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-4-1654604526555-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> to a small bowl with your<strong> red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then set aside until later – this is your <strong>quick-pickled chilli shallot</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1654604533289-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1654604533289-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1654604533289-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1654604533289-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-4-1654604533289-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Tear your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces and add them to one side of a baking tray with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Remove the skin from your<strong> smoked mackerel fillet[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and discard, then add the <strong>skinned mackerel fillet[s] </strong>to the other side of the baking tray, then put the tray in the oven for 6-7 min or until the ciabatta croutons are golden, then remove from the oven and sprinkle <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground sumac </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>over the croutons – these are your <strong>sumac croutons</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1654604546247-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-3-1654604546247-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
